      <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__canps_1ga84d18d801c4f8ab5cc8eeadeff33d8b5" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>s32</type>
        <definition>s32 XCanPs_SelfTest</definition>
        <argsstring>(XCanPs *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XCanPs_SelfTest</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_can_ps" kindref="compound">XCanPs</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function runs a self-test on the CAN driver/device. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The test resets the device, sets up the Loop Back mode, sends a standard frame, receives the frame, verifies the contents, and resets the device again.</para><para>Note that this is a destructive test in that resets of the device are performed. Refer the device specification for the device status after the reset operation.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_can_ps" kindref="compound">XCanPs</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the self-test passed. i.e., the frame received via the internal loop back has the same contents as the frame sent.<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_FAILURE Otherwise.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
If the CAN device does not work properly, this function may enter an infinite loop and will never return to the caller. <linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
 If XST_FAILURE is returned, the device is not reset so that the caller could have a chance to check reason(s) causing the failure. </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
